# Baseline Configuration
# Copy to .env and customize, then run: docker compose up

# === Required ===
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://baseline:baseline@localhost:5432/baseline
AUTH_SECRET=change-me-to-a-random-string

# === GitHub Integration ===
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
GITHUB_TOKEN=
GITHUB_USERNAME=

# === Optional ===
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_key
# CONTACT_EMAIL=you@example.com

# === Advanced (optional networking overrides) ===
# Leave these unset unless you have a non-standard topology. By default the browser
# talks only to the web app, which proxies API calls to the API container; the public
# origin and HTTP/HTTPS scheme are auto-detected per request.
#
# Pin the dashboard's public origin (must match the GitHub OAuth callback URL).
# Leave unset to auto-detect (localhost or a reverse proxy such as the Coder proxy).
# WEB_URL=
#
# Server-side address the web app uses to reach the API over the docker network.
# API_INTERNAL_URL=http://api:3001
#
# Set to call the API directly from the browser on a separate origin (split-origin
# deployments). Leave empty for the default same-origin setup.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=
